- If I give you 5 R chips, I spend 5 of my resources
- If you give me 1 B chip, you're essentially giving me nothing (since I already have an alternative path that doesn't need B)
- My final score would drop from 70 points (independent path) to potentially less

In a "pay for other" mode, I only benefit from a trade if:
1. It saves me chips on my path, OR
2. It allows me to reach the goal when I otherwise couldn't

Neither applies here. You need me far more than I need you.
